# Malaysian Secondary School Students

Schola's primary target users are Malaysian students aged 15-17, with ages 18-22 noted as a secondary segment.

## Reported challenges
- Career choices are shaped by limited exposure and familiar professions.
- Many students become active in career exploration only close to decision deadlines.
- Students struggle to connect education pathways to desired jobs.
- Salary information can be hard to contextualize.
- Familiarity bias narrows aspirations toward known jobs such as teacher, lawyer, doctor, or police.

## Survey signals cited
- 8 out of 10 students lack essential knowledge about chosen careers.
- 7 out of 10 do not actively research career options.
- 6 out of 10 made career choices based on short-term or familiarity factors.
